<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
The Wolves Quest is the Lorien <a href="./HomeQuest">HomeQuest</a>, located in a building to the east of the central area. The Quest can be done with relative ease by any character above lvl 10, and it is possible to do so below this (though not necessarily recommended for newer players). <p>
The quest level is small-medium sized, and divided into a number of small rooms, separated by doors. These are arranged so that there is a central area of six rooms, with a passage all the way around the outside, and three more rooms on each side. 
</p>
<p>
Monsters: The standard wolf, and about half as many Wargs (evil, slightly tougher wolves). 
</p>
<p>
Tactics: The wolves and wargs are all wary of close combat, and do not tend to attack straight off. It is therefore fairly simple to pick them off with ranged attacks. However, it must be noted that when cornered, or if the player is injured, they may attack, and move in to melee. Both the wolves and wargs have few hit points, making them easy to kill. 
</p>
<p>
To complete the quest, simply kill all the wolves and wargs. A yellow message will then appear ('Lothlorien is safer now'). 
</p>
<p>
<strong>N.B.</strong>: It may be difficult to find the last few wolves due to their wariness of close combat. Extensive searching is thus required, or some means of monster detection.  Ranged weapons/spells and lighting or infravision help to track them down. 
</p>
<p>
In addition to the monsters, there are 18 elf skeletons scattered around the level.  Archers may find this significant.... 
</p>
